The Catacombs of Nightfall lie beneath Midgaard's southern chapel quarter.
They began as a sanctioned burial-adjudication institution during the Lantern era: processing the dead, settling debts, archiving oaths.

During the Violet Compact era, the same registry that documented arcane materials entering the Gloamvault catalogued remains here.
Sealed warrants authorized reclassification of unclaimed bodies as "civic remainder."

As Kel'Shadra's influence deepened, burial halls became doctrinal territory.
Administrative processing of the dead became institutional control of memory.
The chapel quarter's bells fell silent during the same suppression cycle as the Gloamvault's Night of Unsounded Bells.

The catacombs connect to the broader Kel'Shadra apparatus through hidden passages.
Undead carry out governance functions. The architecture still sorts the living as though intake processing never ended.
This is procedural horror, not random haunting.
